The focus of the seminar will shift from term to term depending on the needs of interested students. The central focus is on innovative ways to develop reliable software. The seminars alternate between reading papers (spring) and writing (fall).Objectives/eesmärkid:  The chair of programming languages and systems has the goal of improving how software is developed. The aim of the seminar is to assist students to pursue their interests in programming languages and introduce them to cutting-edge developments in software science.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students passing this course will be able to  * read graduate-level textbooks and research literature in the field of programming languages. * give presentation and/or write on a given topic such that it is comprehensible to fellow students.
